oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mrs. D. B. Harrell is standing in front of a 15-acre field of loblolly pine planted in the spring of 1957, near Hixson, Tenn.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Mrs. Harrell planted every one of these loblolly pines herself. These are part of fifteen acres the Harrell's placed in the Soil Bank Program in 1957.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Joe T. Spencer, SCS
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Women; Forests; Pines; Soil conservation; Farms
